problem.markdown:
>>Assume you have to work on very long sequences, and you decide to use an LSTM. Your task strongly relies on long-term dependencies and it is essential to consider all the previous contexts. Can we assume that the LSTM will have no problems given that it can keep the input gate as well as the forget gate completely open at every step?||You only have one attempt for this question.|| <<

(x) No {{Indeed, the internal state and the memory cell vectors have a fixed size. Because of this, the amount of information that can be added to these two vectors is limited.}}
( ) Yes {{Remember that opening a gate means that the information will flow, but we still need a place to store that information.}}
